 This rule provides documentation guidelines and references for working with our Hugo-based documentation site using the Hextra theme.

## Site Configuration

### Core Configuration (hugo.yaml)
- Site title: Forged Apps
- Theme: Hextra (configured as a submodule)
- Main navigation sections:
  - Tech Radar
  - About
  - Search
  - GitHub repository link

### Theme Configuration
- Navbar customization:
  - Custom logo (light/dark variants)
  - Logo width: 124px
- Footer settings:
  - Minimal footer with custom width
  - No copyright/powered by text
- GitHub edit integration enabled
- System-based theme preference

## Content Structure
```
.
├── content/          # Main content directory
│   ├── tech-radar/   # Tech Radar section
│   └── about/        # About section
├── static/           # Static assets
│   └── *.png        # Images including logos
├── layouts/          # Custom layout overrides
├── assets/          # Asset files
├── i18n/            # Internationalization
└── themes/          # Theme submodule
```

### Supported Content Features
1. Raw HTML in Markdown (enabled)
2. Syntax highlighting (with classes)
3. Hextra theme shortcodes:
   - Callout
   - Cards
   - Details
   - FileTree
   - Icon
   - Steps
   - Tabs